9:
Sorry, Mino. 
They'll start nibbling soon.
11: When you catch one, can I eat it?
14:
Not right now, no. 
These are for dinner.
19:
Hmm... I dunno. 
I think we'll dry and preserve those.
22:
Why not eat right away? 
It'll taste better! I wanna eat now!
25:
Well, it's important to have spare food 
to bring with us on quests.
28:
I don't get it! I'm tired of waiting! 
I'll catch my own fish!
35: If you do that, the fish will all swim away.
38:
I'll make us a tasty dinner after this, 
so have a little patience, okay?
42: If you say so. I'll wait.
70: Who are you? Wait your turn.
79:
Forget the fish, Mino! 
Get out of there, quickly!
84:
I said to wait your turn... 
But you didn't listen...
85:
Alk always says... 
to be patient!
91: You... You need to learn some manners!
94: Hold on, Mino, I'll help you!
97:
I'll wait for food, but not this! 
Graaaaugh!
103:
So you took on the Kraken all by 
yourself? Impressive.
107: But... I only cut one tentacle.
111:
Not a lot of people could pull that off, 
you know. 
What's got you so down?
114:
It's my fault... all the fish swam off. 
There's no food for tonight.
118: Always about food with you, isn't it?
120:
Not only that... I couldn't wait. 
Alk told me to be patient.
131:
I present to you my latest culinary 
creation... Kraken and radish stew!
135: The very same one Mino took on? Is this stuff even edible?
143:
Huh... This is rather tasty. 
And it seems we have enough to last 
a good while too.
154: That's right! You did good, Mino.
160:
You sure did! 
So what are you waiting for? Dig in!
